    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-11T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">864.48/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Carroll</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-11T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1920—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 16—10:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Department’s 12, March 4, 6 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d256fn13">Not
                        printed.</note> The Hungarian Chargé d’Affaires informed me today that
                    negotiations, which commenced on January 26, were terminated on the 9th instant
                    by the [signing of agreement] providing for the delivery to Hungary by
                    Yugoslavia of 4,500 car loads of maize, 500 car loads of wheat, 350 car loads of
                    beans and 3,000 pigs. The Yugoslav Government has evinced its apparent intention
                    to execute its undertaking by immediately commencing to effect deliveries. The
                    Hungarian Chargé d’Affaires is inclined to regard as unfounded the statements
                    contained in the second sentence of the telegram under reference to which of
                    course I refrained from alluding. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carroll</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
